    ecosystemDeep: "Brighton’s startup ecosystem has been built on creative digital depth alongside growing SaaS, AI, and GreenTech activity. Wired Sussex has been the long-running trade body for Brighton’s digital media sector for over two decades, coordinating networking, mentoring, investment events, and policy advocacy. The FuseBox, a Wired Sussex initiative, provides innovation space and programmes for digital media startups. Plus X Innovation at Preston Circus offers co-working, labs, and programmes supporting a range of tech and creative startups.\n\nThe University of Sussex Innovation Centre at Falmer supports research spinouts across sciences, engineering, and informatics. Brighton Futures, run by the University of Brighton, handles the university’s enterprise activities and the Green Growth Platform for sustainability startups. Brighton’s creative industries include a substantial games, animation, and digital content cluster where creative industries expenditure credits frequently apply alongside R&D credits for technical development.\n\nThe North Laine and Kemp Town concentrate the creative and tech cluster. The Brighton Dome and Fringe district sustains the theatre, arts, and performance ecosystem where Theatre Tax Relief applies. Angel activity is primarily informal, routed through Wired Sussex events and the Plus X community. Many Brighton creative founders also raise from London angels given the rail link, with mixed Brighton-London syndicates common at all stages. British Business Bank regional funds are accessible through London co-investors.",
