      { question: "How should a Brighton creative tech startup handle the choice between R&D credits and creative industries expenditure credits?", answer: "The key is that R&D credits and creative industries expenditure credits (VGEC, AVEC, Theatre Tax Relief, Orchestra Tax Relief) are mutually exclusive on the same expenditure. For a creative tech startup combining proprietary technology development with content production, the accounting policies at incorporation should separate the two expenditure pools: technical R&D typically qualifying for R&D credits, production expenditure typically qualifying for the relevant creative industries credit. Group structures with holding and production subsidiaries often make the separation cleaner. Submitting your details with a note about your specific business model will help us match you with accountants experienced in your particular relief combination." }
