    introDeep: "Liverpool has been re-shaped by the Liverpool City Region Freeport (with tax sites at the Port of Liverpool, Wirral Waters, and 3MG Widnes) and by continued Knowledge Quarter Liverpool investment across life sciences, IoT, creative industries, and maritime tech. Freeport capital allowances, stamp duty relief, business rates relief, and employer National Insurance relief stack alongside standard UK reliefs for qualifying operations at tax sites. Paddington Village life sciences, Sensor City IoT, Baltic Creative digital industries, and freeport-based maritime and clean energy all support distinct startup patterns.",
    ecosystemDeep: "Liverpool’s startup ecosystem covers a broader sectoral mix than most UK cities of similar size. Knowledge Quarter Liverpool (KQ Liverpool) is the flagship innovation district, bringing together the University of Liverpool, Liverpool John Moores University, Liverpool Hope University, Liverpool School of Tropical Medicine, Royal Liverpool University Hospital, and commercial partners. Liverpool Science Park within KQ Liverpool provides the primary physical base for technology startups.\n\nPaddington Village is the newer life sciences quarter with the Liverpool Life Sciences Accelerator and associated clinical trial infrastructure. Sensor City, a joint venture between the University of Liverpool and Liverpool John Moores University, focuses on IoT and sensor technology startups. Baltic Creative in the Baltic Triangle concentrates creative industries and digital startups. Launch 22 Liverpool and LCR Activate provide incubation and accelerator support.\n\nThe Liverpool City Region Freeport, designated with tax sites at Port of Liverpool, Wirral Waters, and 3MG Widnes, adds capital allowance, stamp duty, business rates, and employer NI relief for qualifying investment. Liverpool 2, the deep-water container terminal, anchors the maritime cluster. Funding flows through the Liverpool City Region Combined Authority, Mersey Angels, Northern Powerhouse Investment Fund II, and national VCs increasingly active in Liverpool deal flow. Life sciences at Paddington Village frequently qualify as R&D-intensive SMEs and KICs, supporting the multi-year development trajectory typical in the sector.",
